        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-13T17:48:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Why do you want to flush the first RT before creating the following ones.\n\nFor memory reasons. Imagine if somebody draws a LOT if BIG atlas items. You don\u0027t want to allocate several 8k x 8k textures upfront. It would be better to create and draw them one at a time, reusing the same texture memory for each atlas. \n\n\u003e I\u0027ve fixed the re-ordering pattern so this should happen after all reordering has occurred.\n\nAwesome!",
      "parentUuid": "52376ff3_542a745d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 86,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 86,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "13d6a9f04d3dd75032cfe461abf44b2db75a9ba4",
